---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Draconis Systems"
  description="Starter privacy policy template for Draconis Systems. Requires legal review before production launch."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Privacy" }]}
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container card stack">
      <p class="badge">Legal Template - Review Required</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>Effective date placeholder: [DD Month YYYY]</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect contact and request details submitted through the website, including name, email, message content,
        and optional project requirements.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Why We Use Data</h2>
      <p>
        Submitted information is used to respond to enquiries, prepare quotes, provide service updates, and maintain
        request records for operational reliability.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Data Processors</h2>
      <p>
        Phase 1 services may include Netlify (hosting/functions), Resend (email delivery), and Supabase (lead record storage).
      </p>

      <h2>4. Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use privacy-friendly analytics focused on aggregate site usage. We do not use analytics to profile individuals.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Retention and Security</h2>
      <p>
        Data is retained only as needed for enquiry handling and business operations, then removed under internal retention policy.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access, correction, or deletion of personal data by contacting
        <a href="mailto:concierge@draconis-systems.co.uk">concierge@draconis-systems.co.uk</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Where applicable, data processing is handled in line with UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018.
      </p>

      <p class="small">This policy is a starter template and requires legal review before launch.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
